1
00:00:57,679 --> 00:00:59,479
The Great Mother has chosen Muifei as the vessel.

2
00:01:00,640 --> 00:01:02,960
The elder will take care of her in place of you.

3
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:03,759
Leave!

4
00:01:03,799 --> 00:01:06,680
I’ve long heard about an uncharted village up there.

5
00:01:06,799 --> 00:01:09,519
The Great Mother atones for all our sins.

6
00:01:09,879 --> 00:01:11,519
How could you let them do this to you?

7
00:01:11,680 --> 00:01:14,560
No human or god can atone for others' sin.

8
00:01:14,840 --> 00:01:16,159
Leave this hell hole.

9
00:01:16,599 --> 00:01:19,319
There are places in the world where you can be happy.

10
00:01:19,560 --> 00:01:20,280
Please come with me.

11
00:01:20,439 --> 00:01:22,200
Leave this hell hole.

12
00:01:22,319 --> 00:01:23,640
Take the Vessel back to the village!

13
00:01:24,079 --> 00:01:25,000
Go!

14
00:01:33,120 --> 00:01:34,120
Are you alright, sweetie?

15
00:01:34,359 --> 00:01:35,120
Mom!

16
00:01:35,680 --> 00:01:37,239
Mom...Mom...

17
00:01:39,120 --> 00:01:40,079
Mom...Mom...

18
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:41,400
Where have you been?

19
00:01:41,760 --> 00:01:44,760
I've been with the sage in the cave near our village.

20
00:01:47,560 --> 00:01:48,560
Mom...Mom...

21
00:01:48,680 --> 00:01:50,480
How did you know I'd be here?

22
00:01:50,719 --> 00:01:52,640
I am always around.

23
00:02:37,400 --> 00:02:38,599
I'm so sorry, sweetie.

24
00:02:39,759 --> 00:02:42,479
I'm so sorry I couldn't help you.

25
00:02:44,439 --> 00:02:45,719
It's alright. Mom.

26
00:02:47,840 --> 00:02:49,039
Mom...

27
00:02:49,759 --> 00:02:52,719
I don't want to be the Vessel anymore.

28
00:02:53,120 --> 00:02:54,280
I'm so sorry.

29
00:02:54,759 --> 00:02:56,800
I'm leaving.

30
00:02:57,560 --> 00:02:58,599
Do you want to come with me?

31
00:02:59,199 --> 00:03:00,439
Are you coming with me?

32
00:03:05,960 --> 00:03:06,960
Where are they?

33
00:03:07,960 --> 00:03:08,960
Spread out!

34
00:03:09,120 --> 00:03:10,000
There!

35
00:03:13,039 --> 00:03:14,400
And where will you go to?

36
00:03:15,120 --> 00:03:16,159
I don't know for now.

37
00:03:17,400 --> 00:03:19,520
I just know that I have to get her out of here now.

38
00:03:19,840 --> 00:03:20,919
And how would you do that?

39
00:03:22,599 --> 00:03:23,199
Why?

40
00:03:23,639 --> 00:03:25,120
Why are you helping my daughter?

41
00:03:28,800 --> 00:03:30,280
I just believe in doing what's right.

42
00:03:31,120 --> 00:03:32,719
There is such a thing as the rule of law.

43
00:03:33,360 --> 00:03:34,719
And what if the law here

44
00:03:35,879 --> 00:03:38,319
and the law down there are different?

45
00:03:39,560 --> 00:03:40,479
I don't care.

46
00:03:42,159 --> 00:03:43,879
I'll take her to the police.

47
00:03:49,159 --> 00:03:50,400
Here, Mui.

48
00:03:55,159 --> 00:03:56,319
Promise me, my sweetie.

49
00:03:57,879 --> 00:03:59,240
No matter what happens,

50
00:04:00,360 --> 00:04:03,360
you'll never take off this necklace.

51
00:04:04,400 --> 00:04:06,360
Promise me.

52
00:04:08,840 --> 00:04:09,800
They're around here.

53
00:04:09,960 --> 00:04:10,879
Find them!

54
00:04:13,360 --> 00:04:14,280
We have to go now.

55
00:04:14,560 --> 00:04:15,719
Take care of Muifei for me.

56
00:04:16,160 --> 00:04:16,680
Ma'am.

57
00:04:16,800 --> 00:04:17,800
You're not coming with us?

58
00:04:18,240 --> 00:04:19,240
I'm sorry, dear.

59
00:04:19,800 --> 00:04:21,560
I can't go just yet.

60
00:04:21,680 --> 00:04:22,399
Why?

61
00:04:22,480 --> 00:04:24,240
I can't go just yet.

62
00:04:24,879 --> 00:04:27,480
Mui! - I promise to look for you.

63
00:04:28,519 --> 00:04:29,319
Mui, we have to go now.

64
00:04:29,360 --> 00:04:30,519
Please take care of her. - Yes, ma'am.

65
00:04:30,600 --> 00:04:31,399
Mui...

66
00:04:31,600 --> 00:04:32,399
Go!

67
00:04:41,600 --> 00:04:42,639
Elder... - What?

68
00:04:42,680 --> 00:04:44,240
Can we ask Luojin to help?

69
00:04:44,399 --> 00:04:45,879
Otherwise they'd get away.

70
00:04:47,319 --> 00:04:48,480
If the sun hasn't set,

71
00:04:49,439 --> 00:04:50,480
Luojin has no power.

72
00:04:53,199 --> 00:04:54,560
Find Muifei.

73
00:04:54,800 --> 00:04:56,079
Don't let her leave the village.

74
00:04:56,720 --> 00:04:57,480
Yes, sir!

75
00:05:13,240 --> 00:05:13,759
Mui.

76
00:05:23,560 --> 00:05:24,480
The key!

77
00:05:25,199 --> 00:05:26,120
Hey!

78
00:05:26,879 --> 00:05:27,879
Dammit!

79
00:05:31,199 --> 00:05:32,279
Hey!

80
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:36,839
Muifei!

81
00:05:44,240 --> 00:05:46,120
After them! Son of a bitc...!

82
00:06:35,480 --> 00:06:37,319
I brought her here to report a crime.

83
00:06:37,839 --> 00:06:38,920
What is the charge?

84
00:06:39,600 --> 00:06:41,240
She's been abused on the hills since she's little.

85
00:06:43,240 --> 00:06:44,800
May I see some identification?

86
00:06:51,199 --> 00:06:53,839
Birth certificate or documents that identify

87
00:06:54,079 --> 00:06:55,240
her place of birth?

88
00:06:58,959 --> 00:07:00,160
She's an illegal, then?

89
00:07:00,639 --> 00:07:01,959
I have to detain her.

90
00:07:02,240 --> 00:07:03,160
Hey!

91
00:07:03,759 --> 00:07:05,480
Who would carry a birth certificate around?

92
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:07,920
You are seriously asking for a document now?

93
00:07:08,319 --> 00:07:10,480
She's been assaulted and abused for decades.

94
00:07:10,920 --> 00:07:12,160
How about you arrest them first?

95
00:07:13,040 --> 00:07:14,000
I understand that.

96
00:07:14,360 --> 00:07:15,600
But I have protocol to follow.

97
00:07:15,639 --> 00:07:16,839
What protocol?

98
00:07:17,600 --> 00:07:19,600
She is here asking for justice,

99
00:07:20,240 --> 00:07:22,480
but you cops are looking to put her behind bars?

100
00:07:23,079 --> 00:07:23,879
Officer...

101
00:07:23,959 --> 00:07:26,120
Those who think they're invicible and hurt her.

102
00:07:26,199 --> 00:07:27,360
You should go catch them first!

103
00:07:28,120 --> 00:07:29,720
Don't you talk about protocol.

104
00:07:30,040 --> 00:07:31,120
Let me ask you something.

105
00:07:31,360 --> 00:07:33,040
If this were your wife and kids.

106
00:07:33,519 --> 00:07:34,519
Would you help them

107
00:07:34,800 --> 00:07:36,160
or ask for their ID?

108
00:07:36,240 --> 00:07:37,199
Kid...

109
00:07:37,279 --> 00:07:38,399
Watch your mouth.

110
00:07:38,439 --> 00:07:39,160
But it's the truth!

111
00:07:39,240 --> 00:07:40,360
Hey! Don't run!

112
00:07:40,439 --> 00:07:41,360
Get out!

113
00:07:41,800 --> 00:07:42,600
Get out!

114
00:07:42,680 --> 00:07:43,720
We’ve got a runner!

115
00:07:43,839 --> 00:07:44,560
Get out!

116
00:07:44,600 --> 00:07:45,639
Give me a sec.

117
00:07:45,839 --> 00:07:47,319
Let me go!  - Freeze!

118
00:07:47,480 --> 00:07:49,680
I don't want to be arrested.

119
00:07:54,480 --> 00:07:55,720
Get out!

120
00:07:55,959 --> 00:07:57,040
Take him!

121
00:08:06,639 --> 00:08:07,680
Have you two done it?

122
00:08:08,319 --> 00:08:09,279
Mom!

123
00:08:09,920 --> 00:08:11,240
That never even crossed my mind!

124
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:16,199
Now Mui is in trouble.

125
00:08:16,839 --> 00:08:18,639
Let her settle down here for a while, Mom.

126
00:08:19,680 --> 00:08:21,319
Our house is not a charity!

127
00:08:21,680 --> 00:08:23,000
I won't take anyone in.

128
00:08:25,720 --> 00:08:27,279
But she's been abused since she was little.

129
00:08:28,480 --> 00:08:30,639
Life up there has been cruel to her.

130
00:08:31,560 --> 00:08:32,720
I wouldn't know that.

131
00:08:33,759 --> 00:08:35,440
Go back, girl.

132
00:08:35,519 --> 00:08:36,480
You can't, Mom!

133
00:08:37,279 --> 00:08:38,600
Let her stay.

134
00:08:39,480 --> 00:08:41,039
She can't go back to that life.

135
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:44,600
She should be somewhere safe to start a new life.

136
00:08:46,200 --> 00:08:47,279
A new life?

137
00:08:47,759 --> 00:08:50,120
You can't get by with your own!

138
00:08:50,559 --> 00:08:52,879
And you'll look after someone else?

139
00:08:53,360 --> 00:08:56,440
You brought an illegal into my shop...

140
00:08:56,639 --> 00:08:57,679
If my shop gets shut down,

141
00:08:57,720 --> 00:08:58,879
we’re all fucked!

142
00:08:59,399 --> 00:09:01,519
Take her to the station if you want to help her!

143
00:09:01,559 --> 00:09:02,639
I did!

144
00:09:03,720 --> 00:09:05,159
Instead of catching the bad guys,

145
00:09:05,320 --> 00:09:06,399
they wanted to put her in jail.

146
00:09:07,080 --> 00:09:08,360
So I brought her here.

147
00:09:09,720 --> 00:09:11,000
To our house.

148
00:09:11,480 --> 00:09:12,879
I thought we were kind.

149
00:09:13,399 --> 00:09:14,799
That we'd offer her help.

150
00:09:14,919 --> 00:09:15,840
But now...

151
00:09:16,080 --> 00:09:17,600
We are just going to push her away?

152
00:09:18,559 --> 00:09:20,320
What the hell made our family turn out like this?

153
00:09:20,360 --> 00:09:21,559
F...ing selfish!

154
00:09:23,279 --> 00:09:24,799
Selfish!?

155
00:09:25,840 --> 00:09:26,720
Huh?

156
00:09:27,840 --> 00:09:29,879
You're calling me f...ing selfish?

157
00:09:31,320 --> 00:09:32,519
Look here!

158
00:09:34,080 --> 00:09:34,879
Here!

159
00:09:35,240 --> 00:09:37,159
This is what responsibility looks like.

160
00:09:37,679 --> 00:09:39,919
It's all in this account!

161
00:09:40,960 --> 00:09:41,879
Do you have any idea

162
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:43,279
how f...king hard I worked

163
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:47,399
to raise you only for you to spit in my face?!

164
00:09:47,879 --> 00:09:48,639
Huh!?

165
00:09:48,759 --> 00:09:50,480
And why am I still doing it anyway?

166
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:52,559
Because I am responsible.

167
00:09:52,840 --> 00:09:54,879
Because I had you!

168
00:09:55,200 --> 00:09:56,879
So I have to take care of you.

169
00:09:57,080 --> 00:09:58,960
This is my selfishness.

170
00:09:59,240 --> 00:10:00,639
And what did you do?

171
00:10:02,240 --> 00:10:04,120
You can't even take care of your own life!

172
00:10:04,440 --> 00:10:06,600
And you're taking care of others?

173
00:10:08,279 --> 00:10:09,799
Let me tell you something, Poom.

174
00:10:10,399 --> 00:10:12,919
Give up your horseshit ideology

175
00:10:13,159 --> 00:10:15,159
and start following my fucking steps!

176
00:10:15,320 --> 00:10:17,080
Get a fucking grip.

177
00:10:20,759 --> 00:10:22,799
Don't waste time trying to turn me into you.

178
00:10:23,360 --> 00:10:24,519
I won't.

179
00:10:25,080 --> 00:10:26,600
My life is my own.

180
00:10:29,200 --> 00:10:30,919
I'll prove it to both of you

181
00:10:31,639 --> 00:10:33,799
that I can make it on my own

182
00:10:34,519 --> 00:10:35,960
without being like you.

183
00:10:37,039 --> 00:10:39,039
I'll take care of her to prove it.

184
00:10:43,600 --> 00:10:44,519
Poom!

185
00:10:44,759 --> 00:10:45,360
Let's go, Mui.

186
00:10:45,399 --> 00:10:46,080
Poom!

187
00:10:46,120 --> 00:10:47,200
Son, where are you going?

188
00:10:47,320 --> 00:10:48,360
Let him!

189
00:10:48,639 --> 00:10:50,399
The likes of him couldn't go far.

190
00:10:50,600 --> 00:10:52,080
He'll come crawling back.

191
00:10:59,720 --> 00:11:01,679
Just take me back home.

192
00:11:04,600 --> 00:11:06,519
Go back to your parents.

193
00:11:11,480 --> 00:11:12,919
But I just got you out.

194
00:11:13,600 --> 00:11:15,320
How could I let you go back.

195
00:11:19,399 --> 00:11:20,399
Mui...

196
00:11:21,559 --> 00:11:23,159
I'll never set a foot back home again.

197
00:11:25,600 --> 00:11:27,039
I'll make it on my own.

198
00:11:32,440 --> 00:11:33,399
But the problem is

199
00:11:36,840 --> 00:11:38,159
I have no money.

200
00:12:16,639 --> 00:12:18,480
149...150...

201
00:12:31,240 --> 00:12:33,360
Do you think we can make it with this money?

202
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:37,200
No idea.

203
00:12:39,919 --> 00:12:41,639
We're not on the hills anymore.

204
00:12:42,519 --> 00:12:44,240
You can stop using your jargons: "goo" and "kor".

205
00:12:45,360 --> 00:12:46,639
I'll teach you.

206
00:12:47,200 --> 00:12:49,120
Out here, people just say 'I'

207
00:12:49,679 --> 00:12:51,840
and call ther other 'You'.

208
00:12:52,720 --> 00:12:54,320
We use honorifics in case we wanna

209
00:12:55,639 --> 00:12:56,360
be polite.

210
00:13:00,039 --> 00:13:01,480
I'm turning 23 this year.

211
00:13:03,320 --> 00:13:05,000
Are you younger or older than me?

212
00:13:10,440 --> 00:13:11,440
So...

213
00:13:11,960 --> 00:13:13,639
Let's say we're the same age.

214
00:13:14,399 --> 00:13:15,519
You can just call me 'Poom'.

215
00:13:26,759 --> 00:13:27,639
And...

216
00:13:30,240 --> 00:13:31,919
Am I making...

217
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:35,519
your life hard?

218
00:13:37,080 --> 00:13:38,000
Mui.

219
00:13:38,720 --> 00:13:40,559
Hardship can't kill anyone.

220
00:13:42,039 --> 00:13:43,519
It makes us stronger.

221
00:13:45,159 --> 00:13:46,440
It teaches to be patient.

222
00:13:48,559 --> 00:13:50,240
To fight for our goals.

223
00:14:01,440 --> 00:14:03,240
We'll go into town.

224
00:14:06,600 --> 00:14:08,480
Find a way to make a living.

225
00:14:14,559 --> 00:14:16,039
Just stick with me, okay?

226
00:14:31,759 --> 00:14:32,720
Say yes.

227
00:14:38,480 --> 00:14:39,519
It looks fine.

228
00:14:40,480 --> 00:14:41,679
How much is the rent?

229
00:14:42,399 --> 00:14:44,720
We don't have to talk prices just now.

230
00:14:45,399 --> 00:14:48,240
I'll bring you the contract tomorrow.

231
00:14:49,480 --> 00:14:50,279
Here's the key.

232
00:14:51,240 --> 00:14:51,919
Unlock it.

233
00:14:51,960 --> 00:14:53,879
The mosquitoes here are brutal!

234
00:14:53,960 --> 00:14:55,000
Unlock and go in.

235
00:14:55,559 --> 00:14:57,679
I’m off! My poker buddies are waiting.

236
00:14:57,840 --> 00:14:59,279
Come on. Go in.

237
00:15:02,840 --> 00:15:03,840
She's in a rush.

238
00:15:08,080 --> 00:15:09,080
Let's go, Mui.

239
00:15:09,440 --> 00:15:10,440
Let's head in.

240
00:15:32,960 --> 00:15:33,919
The lights are out.

241
00:15:35,039 --> 00:15:36,559
So much for taking 'good care' of the house, huh?

242
00:15:50,879 --> 00:15:51,879
The lights are out, Mui.

243
00:15:52,120 --> 00:15:53,000
Are you alright?

244
00:16:01,960 --> 00:16:03,320
Did you hear the water?

245
00:16:05,519 --> 00:16:06,799
She played us for fools.

246
00:16:08,080 --> 00:16:09,080
It's fine.

247
00:16:09,360 --> 00:16:11,000
I'll buy home supplies tomorrow.

248
00:16:11,440 --> 00:16:13,320
And we'll buy clothes too.

249
00:16:44,759 --> 00:16:45,639
Here...

250
00:16:47,159 --> 00:16:48,159
You'll get sick.

251
00:17:03,000 --> 00:17:03,799
Are you tired?

252
00:17:30,480 --> 00:17:31,400
You know what this is?

253
00:17:38,920 --> 00:17:39,920
This here

254
00:17:40,920 --> 00:17:42,279
is called a Walkman.

255
00:17:44,240 --> 00:17:45,720
To listen to music.

256
00:18:20,559 --> 00:18:23,960
Rest you eyes, dear

257
00:18:24,680 --> 00:18:27,440
Into slumber,

258
00:18:27,799 --> 00:18:31,480
Where there's only us two.

259
00:18:35,119 --> 00:18:38,960
Through thick and thin.

260
00:18:39,160 --> 00:18:42,039
Through all the mess.

261
00:18:42,279 --> 00:18:45,559
We just need someone from time to time.

262
00:18:46,400 --> 00:18:51,160
To comfort.

263
00:18:51,839 --> 00:18:55,720
To be understood.

264
00:18:58,599 --> 00:19:01,759
Without a vessel, our village is doomed.

265
00:19:01,960 --> 00:19:02,920
Don't fret.

266
00:19:03,839 --> 00:19:05,200
The elder knows it well.

267
00:19:08,519 --> 00:19:09,920
Muifei will be back for sure.

268
00:19:19,440 --> 00:19:21,119
How could you let them do this to you?

269
00:19:22,799 --> 00:19:24,119
No human or god

270
00:19:24,319 --> 00:19:25,519
can atone for others' sin.

271
00:19:26,119 --> 00:19:27,240
You are not a vessel.

272
00:19:28,440 --> 00:19:29,480
You are a human.

273
00:19:31,480 --> 00:19:33,599
Who falls prey to these sickening minds

274
00:20:01,160 --> 00:20:04,799
Lust will corrupt your soul.

275
00:20:05,200 --> 00:20:06,440
The Great Mother will be furious!

276
00:20:06,640 --> 00:20:08,079
She'll take you to hell.

277
00:20:15,039 --> 00:20:17,079
Go back and ask for her forgiveness.

278
00:20:17,359 --> 00:20:18,839
Go back and be the Vessel!

279
00:20:23,640 --> 00:20:24,400
Mui!

280
00:20:25,599 --> 00:20:26,279
What's wrong?

281
00:20:26,640 --> 00:20:27,319
Luojin!

282
00:20:27,359 --> 00:20:28,079
Luojin was here!

283
00:20:28,279 --> 00:20:29,119
Luojin?

284
00:20:29,960 --> 00:20:30,920
A ghost?

285
00:20:34,319 --> 00:20:35,519
Don't be scared.

286
00:20:36,319 --> 00:20:37,480
We're not on the hills anymore.

287
00:20:38,079 --> 00:20:38,960
No Luojin.

288
